TI  - Social Ties and Foreign Market Entry
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 443
EP  - 469
VL  - 31
IS  - 3
AB  - The social dynamics which precede international exchange are considered in light of data collected on 133 foreign market entries from a sample of highly-internationalized manufacturing firms. Consistent with research done in the social network field, the findings support the hypothesis that knowledge of foreign market opportunities is commonly acquired via existing inter-personal links rather than collected systematically via market research. This study thus contributes towards an understanding of those antecedent conditions that lead to the formation of export exchange relationships.
